-*- Text -*-
This file .../info/dir contains the topmost node of the info
hierarchy.  The "d" command in Info goes here.  This is also the
default node when you start Info.


File: dir	Node: Top	This is the top of the INFO tree.

This is the Directory node of Info.  It contains a menu of all major
topics.  Typing "d" in Info goes here, "q" quits Info, "?" lists all
Info commands, "h" gives a primer for new Info users,
"mEpsilon<Enter>" goes to the Epsilon topic, etc.

* Menu: The list of major topics begins on the next line.

* Epsilon: (epsilon).  Lugaru's Epsilon Programmer's Editor.
